        },
        "block_yc3eGq": {
          "type": "block",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Product Build Up",
            "text": "<p>Using heavy conditioners or styling products can leave a residue that sits on your scalp, weighing hair down and making it look limp and lifeless.</p>",
            "kicker": "Product Build Up",
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/11_imagery_7.png"
          }
        },
        "block_4xFnpM": {
          "type": "block",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Over Washing",
            "text": "<p>Shampooing too often can strip away natural oils, which tricks your scalp into producing even more, creating a frustrating oily cycle.</p>",
            "kicker": "Over Washing",
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/7_46e2c12b-8456-47b9-9166-109d952fe296.png"
          }
        },
        "block_MWVdYE": {
          "type": "block",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Under Washing",
            "text": "<p>However, leaving too long between washes lets oil, sweat and dead skin build up on your scalp, clogging follicles and leaving hair flat and lifeless.</p>",
            "kicker": "Under Washing",
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/11_imagery_8.png"
          }
        },
        "block_Cj9ny8": {
          "type": "block",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Lifestyle Factors",
            "text": "<p>From your diet and daily heat styling to the ever-changing weather, the way you live can easily tip your scalp’s oil balance out of sync.</p>",
            "kicker": "Lifestyle Factors",
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/8_3e829a3a-347c-477d-868c-23bb05b2e457.png"
